\section{Setup Guide}

This SetupGuide is tested on Ubuntu, 
\subsection{Prerequisites}

Git
Vagrant (Version)
Python 3 (Version)
miniconda -> http://conda.pydata.org/miniconda.html

Switch to directory that should later contain your project-source-code

Clone Repository by typing into console:
%text{CODE: git clone https://<<your_username>>@bitbucket.org/kleingeist/spatial-weather.git}

Change directory to spatial-weather

\lstinline{cd spatial-weather}

Install and configure the virtual machine by enter in console:

\lstinline{vagrant up}

While vagrant is setting up your machine you can do the following steps in the meantime:

Create Environment:
You can ignore the error-messages: 
conda: command not found
%bash: /bin/_conda-env-missing: No such file or directory

\begin{lstlisting}
~/miniconda3/bin/conda create --file requirements.conda -n spatial-weather python=3
source ~/miniconda3/bin/activate spatial-weather

pip install -r requirements.txt
pip3 install -r requirements.txt

\end{lstlisting}
